    • Constructor Detail

      • DeviceFactoryImpl

        public DeviceFactoryImpl(ZigBeeApiContext ctx,
                 java.lang.Class<?> cInterface,
                 java.lang.Class<?> cImplementation)
                  throws ZigBeeDeviceException
        Build an DeviceFactory that refine ZigBeeEndpoint by means of cImplementation, into a cInterface service. This factory build the instance of the new service by invoking the constructor cImplementation(ZigBeeApiContext, ZigBeeEndpoint).

        By default the getRefinedInterfaces() is built to return the values:

         cInterface.getDeviceType()
 Device.class.getDeviceType()
        Parameters:
        ctx - ZigBeeApiContext to use for registering the DeviceFactory service
        cInterface - Class representing the refined service that this factory will install
        cImplementation - Class representing the implementation of the refinement service that will be created by the factory
        Throws:
        ZigBeeDeviceException
